<subSubSection pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,1489,2020]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1489,1516]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zhang &amp; Gan, 1986)" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Gan" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Zhang &amp; Gan" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[677,985,1489,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psi">
<emphasis box="[677,694,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[707,740,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">psi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, W. X. &amp; Gan, Y. X." box="[753,977,1489,1516]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="351 - 365" refId="ref76761" refString="Zhang, W. X. &amp; Gan, Y. X. (1986) Description of eight new species of drosophilid flies from Kunming (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Zoological Research, 7, 351 - 365. [in Chinese with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1986">Zhang &amp; Gan, 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the male terminalia, but can be distinguished from the latter by having the aedeagal median rod with 1 pair of lobe-like, distally slender but not bifurcated processes submedially (
<figureCitation box="[418,520,1561,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="65" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1437,1489,2020]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1597,1624]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Description.</emphasis>
Frons dark black above, brown below. Face brown. Gena and postgena black. Mesoscutum, pleura, and scutellum yellowish brown, with dark brown patches and pollinose pattern. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1375,1633,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
): Epandrium pubescent anteroventrally, with ca. 7 setae on posterolateral portion per side (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1226,1669,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus basally with pubescence on outer surface, with several wedge-like prensisetae on apical margin and inner surface (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35B</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral lobe of hypandrium undeveloped and lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1064,1169,1741,1768]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35C</figureCitation>
). Paramere with sparse pubescence subapically; apical process with 1 sensillum and 3 teeth; medial process somewhat triangular; basal process with 1 sensillum (
<figureCitation box="[443,545,1813,1840]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1672,1697]" captionTargetBox="[166,1429,382,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@65.[151,1436,373,1639]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 35. Phortica (Phortica) liukuni Gong &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus (lateral view); B. Surstylus (frontal view); C. Hypandrium, paramere, aedeagus, gonopod, and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3468854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3468854/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 35C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
